{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"zotero":1,"inscriptions":6},{"title":2,"author":3,"date":4,"citation":5},"Iscrizione agonale di Heloros","","1949","\u003Cspan>S. Calderone, «Iscrizione agonale di Heloros», \u003Ci>Epigraphica\u003C/i> 10 (1949): 146–49\u003C/span>",[7],{"file":8,"uri":8,"title":9,"status":10,"editionAuthor":12,"type":13,"objectType":17,"material":21,"condition":25,"layoutDesc":27,"handNote":36,"date":174,"places":179,"geo":188,"provenance":181,"provenanceGeo":192,"country":195,"region":196,"settlement":197,"repository":198,"idno":202,"textLang":205,"tmNumber":209,"facsimile":210,"letterHeights":217,"publications":218,"zotero":226,"keywords":234,"html":246,"bibl":247},"ISic001476","Inscription recording the neaniskoi of the gymnasium",{"_":11},"draft",null,{"_":14,"ana":15,"ref":16},"List","#function.list","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/108.html",{"_":18,"ana":19,"ref":20},"stele.","#object.stele","https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/250",{"_":22,"ana":23,"ref":24},"limestone","#material.stone.limestone","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html",{"ana":26},"#condition.damaged",{"layout":28},{"p":29,"rs":30,"damage":34},"The text fills the face available below the cornice (and seems likely to have continued below), with probably a consistent left margin, but a less regular right margin, and some cramping in order to fit words/phrases to the line (as e.g. in line 1).",{"_":31,"ana":32,"ref":33},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"ana":35},"#text_condition.deteriorated",{"lettering":37,"dimensions":144},[38,39],"The letters are mostly regular with a fairly square module and terminal points to the strokes rather than serifs. Alpha has broken cross-bar; epsilon has nearly equal bars; zeta in the form of an I with broad crossbars; kappa has short arms; mu has sloping outer strokes and half-height mid-strokes; omicron is nearly full-size, and consistently has a central dot (in lines 2 and 3 appears to have a line underneath); rho has rounded closed eye; sigma has horizontal top and bottom strokes, and the mid-strokes extend almost the full width; phi is standard height, elliptical; omega is consistently a closed circle (without the central dot of omicron), sometimes on the baseline, sometimes traversed by the line.",{"_":40,"ref":41},"\n                                    Types list:\n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                    \n                                ",[42,45,48,51,54,57,60,63,66,69,72,75,78,81,84,87,90,93,96,99,102,105,108,111,114,117,120,123,126,129,132,135,138,141],{"_":43,"target":44},"Α type2","https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/cr